column5: Was beautiful here then about 5 minutes ago I couldn't see my boat house (50' away), hope everyone is safe!
Did the wind blow the eye balls right out of you head Cliff?
Nasty here 25 mins ago,could not see across the street. Could be the worst storm of the winter tomorrow and then some ,according to Anthony Farnell.
Foot of snow yesterday, and another 10 cm this morning, now crazy wind gusts!

This will break up ice for sure on Simcoe. Read it,s open water from the oro side to bbp. I watched that wall of snow come in. It was a huge wall and came through quick. Had to put the sunglasses on just to keep the stinging pellets out of the eyes.
Wonder if anyone used common sense and stayed off the ice today.
Did the wind blow the eye balls right out of you head Cliff?  Ya but they hit the garage and bounced right back in
Wind 1 My Roof 0  Time to change your handle from LostAnotherOne to LostAnotherShingle!!!
Time to change your handle from LostAnotherOne to LostAnotherShingle!!! I don't know, "lost another one" still seems to fit if he just puts NF after it
supposed to get around 20cm of snow tomorrow, this wind is just the front of the that storm moving in
10 minutes out of Marham was brutal, sounded like hail. Calmed down some now in Woddy!
Wind has been up good here for last 48-72 hours, still 40 F so just  rain. Tomorrow is trash day so there is going to be bottles, cans and paper blowing down the street

drive home was pretty blustery that 13 caravan I was driving home getting tossed around pretty good up the 35 hwy, seen power was out in Lindsay around 36 and queen so far so good here tonight, the important thing is the beer is still cold
they assume those of us in Lindsay with no power should have it back by 9:45pm.
